DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(87)90034-0
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407687900340
AB  - A parameter truncation criterion, developed in conjunction with Stein's partitioned analog of the Efron and Morris limited translation estimator, is used in an orthonormal linear statistical model setting as a basis for simultaneously selecting the relevant variables and estimating the unknown parameters. Using a squared error loss measure and making use of prior information concerning the coefficients of extraneous variables, the sampling performance of the extended Stein procedure (ESP) is analyzed for two alternative structures of the parameter space and under normal and non-normal errors.
ER  - 
